# New-card compat (wave 3): Wind Drake — PASSIVE Flying evasion keyword.
#
# Wind Drake is a {2}{U} 2/2 with Flying.
#   K:Flying
# (CR 702.9 Flying — can only be blocked by creatures with flying or reach.)
#
# Tracking issue: Card Compatibility: Wind Drake.
#
# Aspects exercised:
#   1. The 2/2 body parses and enters the battlefield.
#   2. Flying evasion: an attacking Wind Drake CANNOT be blocked by a ground
#      creature (a 2/2 Grizzly Bears with neither flying nor reach). The illegal
#      block is rejected and the Drake connects for 2 — proving the evasion is
#      enforced, not merely cosmetic.
#
# Scenario:
#   - P0: a Wind Drake in play (no summoning sickness) ready to attack.
#   - P1: a 2/2 Grizzly Bears (ground, no flying/reach). Because a ground
#     creature has NO legal block against a flyer, the engine never even OFFERS
#     P1 a block action (CR 509.1b) — the proof of evasion is precisely that the
#     block is unavailable. P1 therefore has no script (it can only pass), and
#     the Drake connects for 2.
#
# HOW TO RUN / VERIFY interactively:
#   mtg tui --start-state test_puzzles/newcard_wind_drake_flying_evasion.pzl \
#       --p1 heuristic --p2 heuristic --seed 42 -v 2 --no-color-logs
# The log shows the ground Bears unable to block; Wind Drake deals 2 to P1.

[metadata]
Name:New Card - Wind Drake Flying Evades Ground Blocker
Goal:Win
Turns:1
Difficulty:Easy
Description:P0 attacks with a 2/2 flying Wind Drake; P1's only creature is a 2/2 ground Grizzly Bears that cannot block a flyer (CR 702.9 / 509.1b). The block is rejected and the Drake deals 2, dropping P1 to 18. Backs Card Compatibility: Wind Drake (K:Flying).

[state]
turn=1
activeplayer=p0
activephase=MAIN1
p0life=20
p0hand=
p0battlefield=Wind Drake;Island
p0library=Island;Island;Island;Island;Island

p1life=20
p1battlefield=Grizzly Bears
p1library=Mountain;Mountain;Mountain;Mountain;Mountain

[p0_script]
# Move to combat and attack with the flyer.
PASS_UNTIL phase=declareAttackers
attack Wind Drake

# NOTE: P1 has NO [p1_script]. Its only creature is a ground Grizzly Bears, and
# the engine offers P1 no block action against a flyer (its menu is just
# "play Mountain") — exactly the evasion being tested. P1 passes by default and
# the Drake is unblocked.

[assertions]
# The flyer connected at least once: a ground creature could NEVER block it, so
# P1's life dropped below its starting 20. (The bulk harness runs the full game
# with a heuristic P1, so we assert the monotonic `lt 20` rather than a brittle
# exact total — P1 has no lifegain here, only the unblockable flyer chipping it.)
opponent life lt 20
# Wind Drake is never blockable by P1's ground Bears, so it survives — still in
# play at game end.
me battlefield contains Wind Drake
